  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 22 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1 : 19 \u0b87\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd : \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "22nd Amendment Draft in Next Parliament: Ready to Go Beyond 19th: Justice Minister Vijayadasa",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The 22nd Amendment Bill will be submitted to the House during the next session of the Parliament. Minister of Constitutional Reform and Prisons Affairs Kalanidhi Vijayadasa Rajapaksa has announced that he is ready to go beyond the 19th Amendment.",
        "During yesterday's appointment of the new President Ranil Wickremesinghe's Interim Cabinet, Justice Vijayadasa Rajapaksa, who took charge of the Ministry of Constitutional Reform and Prisons Affairs, said the above while commenting on the next steps to Veerakesari.",
        "He further informed that the 22nd Amendment Bill has been drafted based on making changes in the presidential system of executive power.",
        "Steps will be taken to table the draft in the House in the next parliamentary session. Agreements have also been reached for further amendments to the said draft.",
        "And depending on the current political situation, we are ready to make further amendments to the draft of the 22nd Amendment Bill. In particular, there is scope for amendments to go beyond the 19th Amendment.",
        "He said, \"I request all parties to cooperate to make this process feasible.\"",
        "It is noteworthy that the cabinet gave approval to the basic bill submitted by Minister Vijadasava on the 20th of last month that it has been identified that it is appropriate to amend the constitution in order to create a balance of power between the executive power president and the parliament and hand over some powers to the cabinet and the constitutional council which is jointly responsible to the parliament and the public. ."
      ],
